New Records: X. Curry has a 2-2 record as a pitcher for the Marlins this season.
D. McCaughan has 2 saves as the closer for the Marlins this season.
Y. Rodriguez has a 1-8 record as a pitcher for the Blue Jays this season.
Key Match Events: The Marlins won the series 3-0, securing their first series win against the Blue Jays since 2009.
Dane Myers hit a career-best 5 RBIs with a three-run homer and another homer in the 8th inning.
Griffin Conine had three hits and an RBI for the Marlins.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played at Rogers Centre in Toronto, Ontario, with an attendance of 35,733.
The Marlins' victory marked their 15th win in the series against the Blue Jays.
The game lasted 2 hours and 33 minutes.
Others: The umpires for the game were David Arrieta, Gabe Morales, Chris Guccione, and Ryan Additon.
